# AWS Infrastructure Automation with Terraform

## Overview
This project provisions modular AWS infrastructure using Terraform following Infrastructure as Code (IaC) best practices.

It includes reusable modules for networking, compute, security, storage, databases, and identity management.

## Project Structure

```text
Terraform AWS Infra/
│
├── dev/
│   ├── main.tf
│   ├── variable.tf
│   └── terraform.tfvars
│
└── modules/
    ├── vpc/
    ├── sg/
    ├── ec2/
    ├── alb/
    ├── rds/
    ├── s3/
    └── iam/
```

## Infrastructure Components

### Networking
- Custom VPC module
- Public/private subnet architecture
- Route tables and gateways

### Security
- Modular security group configuration
- IAM roles, policies, and access controls

### Compute
- EC2 provisioning
- Auto Scaling support
- Launch template configuration

### Load Balancing
- Application Load Balancer
- Target groups and listeners

### Storage & Database
- Encrypted S3 bucket provisioning
- RDS deployment in private subnets

## Terraform Modules
This project uses reusable Terraform modules for:

- **vpc** — networking foundation  
- **sg** — security groups  
- **ec2** — compute resources  
- **alb** — load balancing  
- **rds** — relational database  
- **s3** — object storage  
- **iam** — identity and access management  

## Deployment

```bash
terraform init
terraform plan
terraform apply
```

Run from:

```bash
cd dev/
```

